n evaluator exposes spectral balance, dynamic contour, spatial distribution, timbral quality, rhythmic activity, harmonic tension, masking risk, and equal-loudness compensation hints<br/>- feedback can modify future density, register, EQ, dynamics, and sound-palette choices<br/>- tests use synthetic events/audio features to verify correction decisions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 5 | T-005 | Encode SenseWeave voice-to-music interpretation rules. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-014 | — | - room, membrane/contact mic, garden, Theramini, archive, and network sources have musical mappings for pitch, rhythm, density, harmony, timbre, mix, and deference<br/>- Perform-VE condenser/room mic fallback is represented as a source option<br/>- tests verify quiet/noisy room, rain/wind/contact vibration, garden inactivity, Theramini activity, archive recall, and network/weather mappings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 6 | T-006 | Implement ensemble-space and Theramini partner behavior from the course. | T1 | 3 | 3 | MPC-015 | — | - policy supports listening first, complementary register, rhythmic sympathy, harmonic response intervals, accompaniment textures, call/response, imitation, commentary, completion, and silence<br/>- score/tracker metadata identifies current lead/support roles<br/>- tests verify no register crowding, no excessive overlap during human/Theramini gesture, and recovery to solo mode |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 7 | T-007 | Add a genre-literacy strategy library. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-016 | — | - strategies exist for ambient/drone/generative, minimalism, jazz, IDM/electronic, classical/orchestral form, musique concrete/electroacoustic, spectral music, blues, world-music concepts, and post-rock/experimental builds<br/>- strategies can influence form, harmony, rhythm, synthesis, arrangement, and mix without hardcoding imitation<br/>- tests verify strategy selection, arc affinity, and no missing required genre strategy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 8 | T-008 | Make the 30-minute production score executable. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-017 | — | - procedural arc exposes per-phase density, dynamic, harmonic, rhythm, timbre, spatial, compression, SenseWeave, and synthesis targets<br/>- score-tree commissioning and tracker compilation use those targets for long pieces and 5-minute proxy tests<br/>- tests verify the five-phase contour and phase-specific production metadata |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 9 | T-009 | Add phase-transition composition techniques. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-018 | — | - transition planner supports pivot event, breath/silence, metric modulation, timbral morph, harmonic pivot chord, and common-tone bridge<br/>- adjacent sections share at least one continuity element unless a deliberate hard cut is tagged<br/>- tests verify no untagged abrupt phase jumps and valid transition metadata |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Sprint 1 total:** ~27 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 1 | T-001 | Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-010 | — | - CLI or Python API `ablate(score, seeds, disabled_rules=[...])` returns alternate PerformedPart<br/>- output includes a diff report showing which Event fields changed vs. full-stack render<br/>- tests cover single-rule ablation, pair ablation, and all-rules-off (should equal bit-identical Phase-1 baseline) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 2 | T-002 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-011 | — | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 3 | T-003 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-012 | — | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 4 | T-004 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-013 | — | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 5 | T-005 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-014 | — | - `render/rules/agogic.py` detects contour apex (up-down peak) and harmonic_charge peak per phrase<br/>- at apex: duration multiplied by 1.05–1.15, velocity +3–6 dB<br/>- only one apex accent per phrase to avoid caricature<br/>- tests verify apex detection, magnitude, and one-per-phrase rule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 6 | T-006 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-015 | — | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 7 | T-007 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-016 | — | - `render/rules/final_rit.py` applies tempo(x) = v₀·√(1 - α·(x-x_start)/(x_end-x_start)) for cadential phrases only<br/>- α default 0.35, onset position default 0.75 of phrase length<br/>- triggered only when is_cadential=True on phrase<br/>- tests verify curve shape, onset position, and non-application on non-cadential phrases |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 8 | T-008 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-017 | — | - `render/rules/punctuation.py` multiplies terminal-note duration by 1.15–1.40 and inserts breath drawn from Gauss(breath_after_ms, 0.1·breath_after_ms)<br/>- breath counts against R10 silence budget<br/>- tests verify terminal-note extension, breath insertion, and budget accounting |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 9 | T-009 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-018 | — | - `render/rules/articulation.py` sets dur_sec as gate_time × nominal<br/>- repeated-pitch notes slightly shorter (×0.92); notes after upward leaps slightly longer (×1.05)<br/>- tests verify gate-time range per style and contour adjustments |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 10 | T-010 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-019 | — | - `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Sprint 1 total:** ~30 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Sprint 3 — Improvement Engine Hardening\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Sprint 2 — Quality Scoring\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 10 | T-010 | Wire production-course choices into score trees and tracker output. | T1 | 3 | 3 | MPC-020 | — | - score trees carry production vocabulary for mode/scale, harmonic function, meter/groove, counterpoint relation, synthesis architecture, mix role, spatial intent, genre strategy, phase profile, and transition type<br/>- tracker scenes/steps preserve enough metadata for runtime scheduling and diagnostics<br/>- tests verify metadata survives compose -> gate -> compile -> schedule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 11 | T-011 | Extend the composition gate with production-course checks. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-021 | — | - gate can reject phase-inappropriate density, missing harmonic/rhythm metadata, unsafe register, flat dynamics, missing transition continuity, missing mix role, and untagged genre/strategy choices for long pieces<br/>- intentionally sparse/micro pieces can pass when they carry valid sparse intent<br/>- tests cover both rejection and acceptance paths |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 12 | T-012 | Add end-to-end production-course integration tests. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-025 | — | - tests compose, gate, compile, schedule, and inspect a 5-minute proxy arc using production-course metadata<br/>- tests verify non-silent output proxy, no single-note long sections, phase contour, transition continuity, mix role allocation, and repertoire storage<br/>- tests run without live hardware and with mocked SenseWeave/Theramini inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 11 | T-011 | Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-030 | T-001 | - `render/rules/sensor_intent.py` takes raw SenseWeave sensor stream, applies one-pole IIR smoothing (α≈0.1), threshold with hysteresis, and multiplies by sensor→intention weight matrix<br/>- outputs aggregate_intentions, never direct synth parameters<br/>- listener-reverse-engineer test: given recorded sensor stream and rendered output, no single sensor can be shown to drive any single synth parameter at correlation > 0.85 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 12 | T-012 | Implement bounded reactive delta track in scheduler with per-parameter modulation caps. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-031 | T-001 | - scheduler writes sensor_tempo_scale ∈ [0.92, 1.08], sensor_amp_scale ∈ [0.80, 1.20], sensor_brightness ∈ [-1.0, +1.0] onto each Event<br/>- delta track is persisted as JSON alongside audio output for replay<br/>- out-of-bounds values clamped and logged<br/>- tests verify clamping, persistence, and replay consumes the delta track |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 13 | T-013 | Expose aggregate-intention telemetry (global_energy/restraint/brightness) in operator diagnostics, never raw one-to-one mappings. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-033 | T-001 | - `operator_diagnostics.py` extended with aggregate_intentions block<br/>- raw sensor values are NOT surfaced alongside synth parameters in diagnostics (prevents accidentally re-introducing gimmicky reverse-mappings)<br/>- tests verify telemetry shape and absence of raw pairings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 14 | T-014 | Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-034 | T-001 | - `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, MusDr/MusPy for symbolic metrics, librosa for audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty, madmom for beat/tempo cross-check<br/>- documented pass bands from the research: IOI CoV 0.04–0.12, velocity σ 12–22, DNVR 0.25–0.7, pitch H1 2.3–3.0, GS 0.6–0.9, tempo ρ₁ 0.7–0.95, LZ76 0.4–0.7, ≥1 novelty peak per phrase, ≥100 ms silence at phrase boundaries<br/>- tests run metrics on rule-disabled flat-line control (should fail pass bands) and full-stack render (should pass) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 15 | T-015 | Build anti-pattern tests: quantization ghosting, dynamic compression, motif ossification, random-as-expression (Ljung-Box), symmetric-arc uncanny, dead-silence failure. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-035 | T-001 | - `render/antipatterns.py` implements each detector<br/>- quantization ghosting: velocity σ > 0 AND timing σ < 3 ms → fail<br/>- dynamic compression: velocity range < 20 → fail<br/>- motif ossification: GS > 0.95 across repeated sections → fail<br/>- random-as-expression: Ljung-Box fails to reject white noise on tempo or velocity series → fail<br/>- symmetric-arc uncanny: per-phrase worm convex-hull shape variance < 5% across phrases → fail<br/>- dead-silence failure: no rests ≥200 ms in a 2-minute melodic passage → fail<br/>- each detector has a positive fixture (should fail) and negative fixture (should pass) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 16 | T-016 | Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-036 | T-001 | - `render/worm.py` emits per-piece worm JSON and PNG to `artifacts/worms/<piece_id>/`<br/>- convex-hull area computed via scipy.spatial.ConvexHull<br/>- reject point-worm (mechanical: area < 1.0) and space-filling worm (random: area > saturation threshold)<br/>- CI attaches worm PNGs to build artifacts for listener review |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 17 | T-017 | Integrate metric battery + anti-pattern detectors into CI gate with fail-on-regression policy. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-037 | T-001 | - pytest gate runs metrics on a curated fixture set of 5-minute rendered pieces<br/>- any metric outside pass band or any anti-pattern trigger fails the build<br/>- pass bands are per-intent-tag where a