 | T-011 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 22 | T-022 | Implement R10 Silence Budget: per-voice and per-section accumulators enforced at phrase boundaries. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-023 | T-011 | - `render/rules/silence_budget.py` maintains rest_budget += (target_density - actual_density)·dt per voice<br/>- when rest_budget exceeds threshold at phrase boundary, either extends breath (via R6) or drops next phrase to tacet<br/>- tests verify accumulator math, threshold trigger, and tacet-drop path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 23 | T-023 | Implement wind/voice lung-capacity constraints: 4–8 s continuous-play cap per instrument-sim voice. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-024 | T-011 | - voices with lung_capacity set (default 6 s for winds/voice, null for others) track continuous sounding time<br/>- exceeding cap forces a breath at next phrase boundary or earlier if density tolerates<br/>- tests verify cap enforcement and breath insertion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 24 | T-024 | Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-025 | T-011 | - `render/rules/call_response.py` reads leader voice's PerformedPart and transforms follower's PerformanceIntent before follower render<br/>- leader build → follower descends from apex; leader pause → follower fills<br/>- respects existing role metadata (leader/follower/solo/tacet) from production-course PRD<br/>- tests verify complementarity on 2-voice fixture |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 25 | T-025 | Compose SectionEnvelope with phrase arcs multiplicatively so section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-026 | T-011 | - at each event, final_tempo_mult = section_envelope.tempo_base(t) × phrase_arch.tempo_mult(x) × (1 + sensor_tempo_scale)<br/>- clamp composed result to ±15% bounds<br/>- tests verify multiplicative composition and clamp behavior |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 26 | T-026 | Implement tempo-dependent swing curve per Friberg/Sundström (3.5:1 at slow tempi down toward 1:1 at fast), with short-note near-constant ~100 ms. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-027 | T-011 | - swing ratio computed from current tempo rather than fixed global setting<br/>- short-note duration held near 100 ms across tempo range<br/>- optional role-specific override (cymbal uses ride ratio, soloists use Benadon BUR 1.2–1.7)<br/>- tests verify ratio curve and short-note invariance |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 27 | T-027 | Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-028 | T-011 | - arc_shape selected from PerformanceIntent or, if unspecified, sampled from authored distribution weighted by intent_tag<br/>- for intent_tag=withhold, occasional flat arc (tempo_deviation_pct=0) is expressive<br/>- tests verify shape distribution over many phrases and flat-arc presence for withhold intent |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 28 | T-028 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-029 | T-011 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Sprint 3 total:** ~30 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Sprint 5 total:** ~24 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Sprint 5 — Library & CRUD Polish\\\\\\\\