ecursive_composer.py` and `score_tree.py` extended to attach PerformanceIntent to every phrase node and SectionEnvelope to every section node<br/>- composer accepts an explicit composition_seed argument and produces byte-identical score trees for the same seed + brief<br/>- existing pieces still compose successfully; gate passes on unchanged repertoire<br/>- tests verify determinism (two runs same seed → equal score-tree hash) and metadata presence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 36 | T-036 | Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-008 | T-001 | - OSC bundle schema documented in `my-claw/docs/render-osc-schema.md`<br/>- `music_tracker_runtime.py` serializes Event fields into Pbind-compatible dictionaries preserving rule_stack and seed_path<br/>- synth side (reference SC file under `my-claw/supercollider/render_contract.scd`) demonstrates reading and ignoring unknown keys gracefully<br/>- tests verify round-trip of a sample phrase through serialize → parse preserves all fields |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 37 | T-037 | Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-009 | T-001 | - `render/replay.py` exposes replay(score, seeds, delta_track) returning PerformedPart byte-identical to original<br/>- delta_track is persisted as JSON per run alongside audio output<br/>- tests verify: re-render with same inputs produces identical Event sequence (hash match) including all timing, velocity, and articulation values |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Sprint 5 total:** ~27 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -57,21 +83,20 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|---