\\\\\\\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+def verify_resolution(leader_notes: tuple[int, int], follower_notes: tuple[int, int]) -> bool:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    Verify resolution-completion for a single interval transition.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    If the first vertical interval is a sharp dissonance, both voices\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    must move stepwise (0, 1, or 2 semitones) to resolve it.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    initial_interval = interval_between(leader_notes[0], follower_notes[0])\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    if initial_interval.consonance != \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sharp_dissonance\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        return True\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    leader_motion = abs(leader_notes[1] - leader_notes[0])\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    follower_motion = abs(follower_notes[1] - follower_notes[0])\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    return leader_motion <= 2 and follower_motion <= 2\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+def voice_leading_smoothness(leader_notes: tuple[int, ...], follower_notes: tuple[int, ...]) -> float:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    Calculate voice-leading smoothness scoring for a pair of voices.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    Returns the average size of leaps (in semitones) across all melodic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    intervals in both voices. A lower score means smoother voice-leading.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    total_motion = 0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    intervals = 0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\