CHANGELOG.md:91:- Added depth-2 end-to-end accompaniment test coverage (frac-0055): `tests/test_accompaniment.py` now ships a new `TestAccompanimentEndToEnd` class that drives the existing Korsakov accompaniment public surface (`DensityTracker`, `select_accompaniment_type`, `breathing_swell`, `should_transition_gradually`, `should_pedal`, `pedal_note`, `get_pattern`, and the six pattern generators) through end-to-end multi-step pytest methods. The new tests sweep the documented density bands and verify the inverse-density rule, iterate every pattern type 1-6 to assert non-empty events with positive amps/releases, sweep `breathing_swell` over rest/active/edge inputs, walk full phrase boundaries through `should_pedal` + `pedal_note`, run the dense-melody and resting-melody pipelines end-to-end through a synthetic `DensityTracker` window, and pin a six-bar composer loop. A `test_test_accompaniment_reaches_depth_two` gate test asserts the file's fractal classification is at least depth 2. Existing `TestDensityTracker`, `TestSelectAccompanimentType`, `TestPatterns`, `TestPedalPoint`, `TestBreathing`, and `TestTransition` assertions are preserved unchanged; `tests/test_accompaniment_depth.py`, `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:93:- Added depth-2 pytest collection gate reports (frac-0054): `tests/conftest.py` now exposes a frozen `CollectionGateDecision` dataclass plus `collection_gate_decisions`, `apply_collection_gate_decisions`, and `summarize_collection_gate_decisions` so tests and diagnostics can inspect live/host-specific marker gates with enabled state, skip reason, matched count, skipped count, and JSON-safe totals. Existing `--run-live-modal`, `--run-live-replicate`, `live_modal`, `live_replicate`, and `cypherclaw_e2e` behavior is preserved: Modal/Replicate live tests skip by default unless opted in, and CypherClaw e2e skips on CI. `tests/test_conftest_depth.py` pins hook registration, default and CI gate behavior, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:95:- Added depth-2 test_genai smoke probe (frac-0053): root-level `test_genai.py` is now a typed module exposing a frozen `GenAIProbeResult` dataclass plus `create_genai_client`, `list_model_names`, `probe_genai_client`, `summarize_probe_result`, `format_probe_lines`, and `main` so callers, tests, and operator dashboards can drive `probe → summarize → render → main` without re-implementing the conditional script logic. The success path returns a populated result with the sampled model names; any raised `Exception` is folded into an `ok=False` result with the stringified error and zero models. `summarize_probe_result` is JSON-safe (`sampled_models` rendered as a list); `format_probe_lines` preserves the original CLI output format byte-for-byte ("Successfully created client without explicit API key." header plus per-model lines on success, single "Error: <error>" line on failure); `main()` runs the probe and prints each line, returning exit code 0 to match the original `python test_genai.py` smoke behavior. `tests/test_test_genai_depth.py` pins the new probe surface, client construction (explicit key + default-auth env), limit-respecting model sampling, success/error result paths, JSON-safe summary, canonical CLI line rendering, end-to-end main, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` and the startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:97:- Added depth-2 temp sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0052): root-level `temp_sampler_dispatch.py` is now import-safe outside the SenseWeave package and exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan`. The helpers produce JSON-safe operator output for sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and canonical `/s_new sw_sampler` synth args. `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` builder while preserving existing buffer loading, FX preset, handle-release, fire-and-forget, and sustained lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_temp_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins import safety, meaningful plan/summary output, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2; production sampler dispatch tests and startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:99:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw memory journal helpers (frac-0051): `promptclaw/memory.py` now exposes a frozen `MemoryEntry` dataclass plus typed helpers `format_run_block`, `parse_memory_log`, and `summarize_memory_log`, and `MemoryStore` gains `entries`, `latest_entry`, and `summary` read-side methods so callers and operator diagnostics can render a single run's memory block, parse the project memory file back into structured entries (run id, title, status, lead, verifier, final phase, body), and emit a JSON-safe aggregate (entry count, latest run id, sorted status counts, sorted lead-agent counts excluding the `n/a` placeholder). `MemoryStore.append_run_summary` now delegates block rendering to `format_run_block` so the on-disk markdown shape stays byte-identical for orchestrator clarification-pause and final-summary writes. `tests/test_promptclaw_memory_depth.py` pins canonical block layout, `n/a` agent fallbacks, append/parse round-trip, empty-input handling, JSON-safe summary aggregation, `n/a` lead exclusion, store read helpers (including missing-file path), and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` remains the regression anchor for end-to-end run behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:101:- Added depth-2 image API schema summaries (frac-0050): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/schemas.py` now exposes `TERMINAL_JOB_STATUSES`, `ACTIVE_JOB_STATUSES`, frozen `JobLifecycleSummary` and `InternalSpecProfile` dataclasses, and typed helpers `is_terminal_status`, `build_job_lifecycle_summary`, `summarize_status_response`, `build_internal_spec_profile`, and `summarize_internal_spec`. The helpers give operator logs and dashboards JSON-safe lifecycle/spec metadata including terminal-state classification, output counts, error flags, image dimensions, pixel count, megapixels, prompt previews, style presence, model overrides, and content-piece IDs without changing any Pydantic request/response fields or runtime behavior. `tests/test_image_api_schemas_depth.py` pins the new helper surface and fractal depth >= 2; existing parser, worker, app, jobs DB, S3 uploader, startup identity, and narrative ASGI startup anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:103:- Added depth-2 image API S3 uploader reports (frac-0049): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/s3_uploader.py` now exposes module-level `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL`, `DEFAULT_CONTENT_TYPE`, and `CONTENT_TYPE_BY_EXTENSION` constants plus a frozen `UploadReport` dataclass and typed helpers `guess_content_type`, `categorize_upload_size`, `build_upload_report`, `summarize_upload`, and `summarize_upload_report` so worker batches and operator dashboards can map filenames to canonical MIME types, aggregate `UploadResult` records into bucket / object-count / total-bytes / keys / urls reports, classify byte sizes into empty/small/medium/large bands, and emit JSON-safe per-result and per-batch summaries. `upload_image` keeps its keyword-only signature, single `put_object` call, and direct-S3 URL contract; the cache-control header is now sourced from `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL` rather than a literal. `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader_depth.py` pins MIME classification (known + unknown + missing suffix), batch aggregation, empty-iterable handling, size-band thresholds, JSON-safe summaries, the cache-header contract, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader.py` remains the regression anchor for existing upload behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:105:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw scaffold template reports (frac-0048): `promptclaw/templates.py` now exposes frozen `ScaffoldTemplateEntry` and `ScaffoldTemplateReport` dataclasses plus typed helpers `template_category`, `required_startup_prompt_paths`, `scaffold_template_entries`, `scaffold_template_report`, and `summarize_scaffold_templates` so callers can inspect generated starter scaffold files by category, byte size, required startup prompt coverage, and JSON-safe per-entry rows. Existing `project_scaffold(project_name)` output is preserved exactly for bootstrap and CLI init consumers. `tests/test_promptclaw_templates_depth.py` pins category classification, scaffold contract preservation, report totals/category counts, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; bootstrap/config/orchestrator and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:107:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw config status reports (frac-0046): `promptclaw/config.py` now exposes a frozen `ConfigStatusReport` plus typed helpers `enabled_agents`, `config_status_report`, `summarize_config`, and `load_or_default` so callers can inspect the project name, artifact root, control-plane mode/agent, default task type, agent count, sorted enabled/disabled agent name tuples, and validation issues in one diagnostic call. `enabled_agents` returns deterministic alphabetical names; `summarize_config` is JSON-safe and exposes lists rather than tuples; `load_or_default` returns the persisted config when `promptclaw.json` is present and otherwise returns `default_project_config(project_name)` without writing to disk. Existing `default_project_config`, `config_path`, `load_config`, `save_config`, and `validate_config` signatures and behavior are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_config_depth.py` pins enabled-agent ordering, default and invalid-config status reports, JSON-safe summary lists, the load-or-default branch, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_config.py` remains the regression anchor for existing load/validate behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:109:- Added depth-2 composer quote verification reports (frac-0045): `my-claw/tools/composer_quote_verify.py` now exposes a frozen `QuoteVerificationReport` plus typed helpers `build_quote_verification_report`, `summarize_quote_verification_report`, `render_quote_verification_lines`, and `quote_verification_exit_code` around the existing hardware-free known-room/self-quote smoke path. The report captures descriptor identity/tags, requested/captured piece counts, song ids, match details, overlap, score, and status while preserving `trigger_composer_pieces`, `find_motif_tag_match`, and the CLI's existing success/failure output and exit codes. `tests/test_composer_quote_verify_depth.py` pins the end-to-end report, JSON-safe summary, CLI line rendering, failure-status exit mapping, and fractal depth >= 2; original composer quote, sample capture, self-listener, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:111:- Added depth-2 hook schema rewriter (frac-0044): `rewrite_hook.py` is now an importable module with a frozen `HookRewriteResult` dataclass plus typed helpers `apply_field_renames`, `migrate_file`, `apply_hook_rewrites`, and `main`, sourced from a canonical `HOOK_FIELD_RENAMES` table (`("hook_type", "hook_class")`, `("rhythm_cell", "rhythm")`) and `HOOK_TARGET_FILES` listing the five SenseWeave files the original one-shot script wrote to. The previous body of unconditional regex/`str.replace` calls — which left an already-migrated tree corrupted with duplicate dataclass fields and a broken `return HookProfile(...)` block when re-run — is replaced by an idempotent rename: `apply_field_renames` is pure string-in/string-out, `migrate_file` only writes when the produced text differs from disk and reports `existed`/`changed`, missing files report `existed=False` without raising, and `apply_hook_rewrites(root)` walks `HOOK_TARGET_FILES` in declared order returning one `HookRewriteResult` per target. `main()` prints a `rewrote`/`unchanged`/`missing` line per result and exits 0; `if __name__ == "__main__"` is preserved. `tests/test_rewrite_hook_depth.py` pins canonical-rename, idempotency, write-on-change, no-op-on-migrated-file, missing-file handling, declared-order tree migration, end-to-end idempotency on a migrated tree, the canonical rename table, and fractal depth >= 2; senseweave hook tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:113:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw artifact run reports (frac-0043): `promptclaw/artifacts.py` now exposes frozen `ArtifactFileStatus` and `ArtifactRunReport` dataclasses plus `ArtifactManager.build_run_report()` so callers can summarize expected run files, present/missing counts, missing file names, event count, and latest event type from the canonical `ProjectPaths.run_layout()` and existing event log. Existing artifact write helpers, `read_events()`, JSONL event shape, and on-disk `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` filenames are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_artifacts_report.py` pins written-artifact summaries, JSON-safe report output, and fractal depth >= 2; existing artifact depth tests and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:115:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw SDP cost roll-ups (frac-0042): `promptclaw/sdp_cost.py` now exposes `total_cost_usd()`, `cost_by_model()`, `aggregate_rows()`, and `summarize_cost_run()` plus a frozen `CostRunSummary` dataclass so operator/CI callers can compute summed daily cost, partition cost across declared model tiers (with rows whose `models` list is empty bucketed under `fallback`, matching `match_pricing`'s sentinel), aggregate runs / token columns / cost into a single `DailyCostRow`, and run extract → CSV write → optional Markdown cap summary in one call. Existing `match_pricing`, `call_cost_usd`, `extract_steady_state_cost`, `write_csv`, `read_csv`, `check_daily_caps`, `summarize_daily_cap`, `render_cap_summary`, `write_cap_summary`, `_parse_args`, and `main` signatures, the on-disk CSV header, and the committed cap summary output are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_sdp_cost_depth.py` pins total / by-model / aggregate roll-ups, end-to-end CSV+cap output, the no-cap-path branch, public-surface preservation, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` and `tests/test_sdp_telemetry_cost_model.py` remain the regression anchors for extractor pricing and CLI behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:117:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw path layouts (frac-0041): `promptclaw/paths.py` now exposes a frozen `RunPathLayout` plus `ProjectPaths.run_layout()`, `ProjectPaths.ensure_run_layout()`, and `ProjectPaths.path_summary()` so project/run filesystem contracts can produce typed layouts, idempotently prepare run directories, and emit JSON-safe operator summaries. Existing project-level path attributes and `run_*` helper return values are preserved; `ArtifactManager.create_run_layout()` now iterates the canonical run layout while keeping the same on-disk `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` structure. Empty run ids fail fast with `ValueError` before layout creation. `tests/test_promptclaw_paths_depth.py` pins helper compatibility, JSON-safe summaries, layout preparation through `ArtifactManager`, run-id rejection, and fractal depth >= 2; config, orchestrator, artifact, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:119:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw artifacts read path (frac-0040): `promptclaw/artifacts.py` now exposes `ArtifactManager.read_events()` which parses `events.jsonl` line by line and reconstructs the same `Event` dataclass shape that `append_event()` writes, returning `[]` when the log file does not yet exist. The four filename-taking write helpers (`write_prompt`, `write_output`, `write_handoff`, `write_summary`) now reject empty/whitespace-only filenames with `ValueError` before any I/O, matching the orchestrator's existing call-site contract while failing fast at the boundary. Existing public method signatures, on-disk filenames, JSONL serialization shape, and orchestrator call sites are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_artifacts_depth.py` pins the round-trip read, missing-log empty result, empty-filename rejection across the four filename helpers, normal-filename acceptance, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` and `tests/test_config.py` remain the regression anchors for end-to-end run behavior and config loading.
CHANGELOG.md:121:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw model diagnostics (frac-0039): `promptclaw/models.py` now exposes a frozen `ConfigModelReport` plus typed helpers `sorted_agents`, `summarize_agent`, `config_model_report`, `summarize_config_model`, `summarize_route_decision`, and `summarize_run_state` so config, route, agent, and run dataclasses can emit deterministic JSON-safe operator summaries without changing existing dataclass fields or orchestration call sites. The narrative ASGI entry point `cypherclaw.narrative_api.main:app` now calls `bootstrap_identity()` before app creation, matching the `python -m cypherclaw.narrative_api` startup path so first boots mint and persist identity automatically. `tests/test_promptclaw_models_depth.py` pins model summary counts, sorted JSON-safe output, route/run summaries, an end-to-end orchestrator run summary, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_narrative_api_main.py` now pins ASGI import identity persistence between boots, while existing config/router/orchestrator and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:123:- Added depth-2 trust manager planning (frac-0038): `promptclaw/coherence/trust.py` now exposes a frozen `TrustEventPlan` plus `trust_event_plans()` returning the canonical `hard_violation`, `soft_violation`, and `compliant_action` plans sourced from `TrustManager.HARD_PENALTY`, `SOFT_PENALTY`, and `COMPLIANT_REWARD`. `TrustManager.apply_event(agent, plan)` is the single mutation path — it validates the counter field against the canonical set, clamps the new score to `[0.0, 1.0]`, increments the named counter, touches the timestamp, and returns the new score. The legacy `apply_hard_violation`, `apply_soft_violation`, and `apply_compliant_action` methods now route through `apply_event` with the canonical plans so existing penalty/reward and clamp behavior is preserved. `apply_event_by_name`, `restricted_agents`, `summarize_agent`, and `fleet_summary` give operator surfaces a JSON-safe report with the configured constants, restriction threshold, alphabetically-ordered per-agent rows, and restricted-agent count. `tests/test_trust_depth.py` pins the canonical plan, apply-event routing, legacy-method delegation, JSON-safe sorted summary, unknown-counter rejection, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_trust.py` remains the regression anchor for existing penalty/reward, clamping, restriction-threshold, and multi-agent isolation behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:125:- Added depth-2 entities-domain migration planning (frac-0037): `narrative/migrations/20260502_001347za_add_entities_domain.py` now exposes a frozen `DomainColumnPlan` plus `domain_column_plans()` and `domain_migration_summary()` so the CN-001 migration can report its canonical `entities` / `events` domain-column plan, generated upgrade SQL, reverse downgrade targets, revision id, and default domain in JSON-safe form. `upgrade()` and `downgrade()` now execute through the same plan while preserving the existing `domain TEXT DEFAULT 'shared'` behavior for existing rows, new explicit domain values, and downgrade/re-upgrade. `tests/test_narrative_entities_domain_migration.py` pins the plan, summary, existing SQLite migration behavior, and fractal depth >= 2; narrative entity API and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:127:- Added depth-2 Theramini MIDI listener (frac-0036): `my-claw/tools/theramini_midi.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `midi_to_freq`, `midi_to_name`, `parse_midi_messages`, `apply_midi_event`, `process_buffer`, `render_state`, `write_state`, `read_midi_buffer`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus frozen `MidiEvent` and mutable `MidiState` dataclasses that hold the current note, last-note timestamp, silence-start timestamp, CC map, and pitch-bend value. The listener parses raw Note On / Note Off / CC / pitch-bend bytes (including the velocity-zero Note On = Note Off and 2-byte program/channel-pressure cases), folds events into a per-cycle `MidiState`, and atomically writes `/tmp/theramini_state.json` with the existing consumer contract (`timestamp`, `is_playing`, `pitch_hz`, `pitch_note`, `pitch_confidence`, `state`, `consecutive_silence_ms`, `midi_cc`, `pitch_bend`) after passing through `senseweave.theramini_duet.normalize_theramini_state` so the duet conversation contract is preserved. `is_playing` decays to `False` after `2.0` seconds without a fresh note. Loop control gains `--device`, `--interval`, `--state-path`, `--once`, and `--max-iterations`; missing or unopenable MIDI devices fall back to the existing `state="no_device"` payload shape. `tests/test_theramini_midi.py` pins import safety, MIDI parse/apply, active-note and silent-window rendering, end-to-end fd writes, and the no-device fallback; `tests/test_theramini_listener_runtime.py`, `tests/test_theramini_duet.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:129:- Added depth-2 Tamagotchi diagnostics (frac-0035): `my-claw/tools/tamagotchi.py` now exposes frozen `PetVitalSnapshot` and `PetFleetReport` dataclasses plus typed helpers `pet_health_band`, `pet_activity_band`, `xp_to_next_stage`, `stage_progress_fraction`, `pet_attention_reasons`, `build_pet_vital_snapshot`, `build_pet_fleet_report`, and `summarize_pet_fleet_report`. Existing JSON persistence, task XP, idle decay, and GlyphWeave display contracts are preserved, while `PetManager.fleet_report()` now gives status/diagnostic callers an end-to-end health/activity/fleet summary with canonical pet ordering, aggregate XP/tasks, mean vitals, active/sleeping/attention agents, and XP leader. `tests/test_tamagotchi_depth.py` pins helper bands, frozen snapshot/report shape, JSON-safe summaries, persistence round-trip, and fractal depth >= 2; existing tamagotchi/GlyphWeave tests and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:131:- Added depth-2 startle daemon processing (frac-0034): `my-claw/tools/startle_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `read_room_activity`, `amp_from_room`, `update_baseline`, `baseline_value`, `render_output`, `write_output`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus a `DaemonState` dataclass that combines the existing `senseweave.startle.StartleState` with a rolling-baseline tracker. The daemon now reads `/tmp/room_activity.json`, takes the louder of `window_mic_amp` / `cypherclaw_mic_amp`, maintains a 20-sample rolling-median baseline (with a non-zero floor so the detector never sees a degenerate baseline), runs the existing `update_startle` rules, and atomically writes the consumer contract (`startled`, `startle_count`, `cooldown_active`, `face_reaction`, `should_mute`, `amp`, `baseline`, `timestamp`) consumed by `inner_life.world_model.poll_state`. Loop control gains `--once`, `--interval`, `--room-path`, `--state-path`, and `--max-iterations`; existing `senseweave.startle` rules are unchanged. `tests/test_startle_daemon.py` pins import safety, baseline/amp helpers, end-to-end loud-room startle output, and quiet-room loop output; `tests/test_startle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:133:- Added depth-2 sensory journal daemon processing (frac-0033): `my-claw/tools/sensory_journal_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers for reading fused organism state, normalizing Theramini/room/mood snapshots, detecting ordered Theramini-start, room-transient, and energy-shift events, writing through the existing `senseweave.sensory_journal` JSONL contract, and running the loop with `max_iterations` / `--once` for tests and smoke runs. `tests/test_sensory_journal_daemon.py` pins import safety, meaningful event descriptions, one-cycle journal writes, and duplicate suppression across repeated active cycles; the existing sensory journal suite and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:135:- Added depth-2 voice alias report helpers (frac-0032): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/voice_aliases.py` now exposes frozen `VoiceAliasEntry` and `VoiceAliasReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `voice_namespace`, `voice_alias_family`, `is_aliased_voice`, `iter_alias_pairs`, `aliases_for_target`, `alias_chain`, `build_voice_alias_entry`, `build_voice_alias_report`, and `summarize_voice_alias_report` so runtime/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing eleven-entry `RUNTIME_VOICE_ALIAS` table into a JSON-safe summary with ordered source/target voices, namespace counts (core vs senseweave), family counts (struck_tonal, metallic, granular, drum, other), senseweave-variant and core-alias counts, unique-target count, target-to-sources mapping, and per-alias entries flagging `is_senseweave_variant` and `is_changed`. Existing `resolve_runtime_voice_name` lookup behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_voice_aliases_depth.py` pins helper outputs, frozen entry/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with `resolve_runtime_voice_name`, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_voice_aliases.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
